As Florida recounts votes county by county, one major issue of contention is unclear signatures on ballots, particularly those that were mailed in. Thousands were rejected 
Young people’s ballots are the ones most often thrown out, with some speculating that they don’t use their own handwriting enough to develop a consistent signature. Some research has also shown that signatures change as people age or become ill, or if they are in a rush.
